Kosovo at the current moment

At the current moment, although Serbs strongly reject this solution, Kosovo, with substantial support of the West, is planning to become a member of all organizations available inside UN, like UN Security Council, UN General Assembly, UN Human Rights Council and others. This is in accordance with regulations established by the UN since Kosovo is not an independent state, and therefore cannot be a member in UN?.

We will take a look at those organizations one by one in the second part of this article.

Summarizing previous parts, Kosovo Albanians strongly believe that they have fully legal grounds to claim independence of Kosovo, because Albanians form important minority in Montenegro and Macedonia as well. On the other hand, most Serbian inhabitants in autonomous province of Kosovo have been also citizens of Serbia for multiple reasons, but most of them were non Albanian

Serbian noblemen inherited property, so they did not emigrate, or they determined that majority life style, plus good relations with Albanians are perfect balance for their lives in the south. Therefore, if Albanians succeed with their claims of independence for Kosovo, they will try to repeat this claims in those two republics.
